  "text": "2/2 mice were more susceptible to EMCV infection [CITATION_1] . It is interesting to note that enteroviruses such as EMCV do not activate RIG-I, and the host defence depends on the TLR3 and IFN-c pathway. Influenza, however, is a potent activator of RIG-I, and thus this may be the key difference between these two opposite phenotypes associated with infection of TLR3 2/2 mice. TLR3 2/2 mice were protected in an experimental model of polyI : C-induced shock and TLR3 2/2 mice responded with attenuated IL6, IL12p40 and IFN-c profiles . But this profile of cytokine induction was not observed in H5N1-infected TLR3 2/2 mice.",
